TITLE: Judge denies Sen. Lindsey Graham's bid to delay testimony before Trump Georgia grand jury election probe
SUMMARY: Fulton County District Attorney Fani Willis is investigating possible interference in Georgia's 2020 election by former President Donald Trump and his allies.

TITLE: House Democrats urge Twitter, TikTok, Meta and others to address spike in threats against law enforcement after FBI search of Trump home Mar-a-Lago
SUMMARY: Statements from GOP leaders including Trump, Kevin McCarthy and Mike Pence "coincided" with a rise in belligerent online rhetoric, Maloney and Lynch wrote.

TITLE: A parody Twitter account created by a paralegal mocking Dr. Oz's 'crudites' campaign video goes viral
SUMMARY: A paralegal and graphic designer teamed up to mock Dr. Mehmet Oz's video showing him mispronouncing the name of a Redner's grocery store.

TITLE: Walmart expands abortion coverage for its employees in the wake of Roe v Wade decision
SUMMARY: The retailer is the nation's largest employer with about 1.6 million employees.

TITLE: Judge says some of DOJ's affidavit used to obtain Mar-a-Lago search warrant can be unsealed
SUMMARY: The DOJ had asked Magistrate Judge Bruce Reinhart not to unseal the affidavit, arguing that it could compromise the probe involving Trump's Mar-a-Lago home.

TITLE: Michigan governor's race could cost $100 million as billionaire DeVos family spends millions to oust Gov. Gretchen Whitmer
SUMMARY: One GOP strategist estimates Michigan's governor's race could cost between $75 million and $100 million with the DeVos' spending on the campaign.

TITLE: U.S. to provide 50,000 monkeypox vaccines for Pride and other events with high attendance by gay men
SUMMARY: The U.S. has delivered more than 1 million doses of the monkeypox vaccine across the country since the outbreak started in May, according to HHS.

TITLE: Fetterman campaign says it raised $500,000 in 24 hours after Dr. Oz's viral crudites video
SUMMARY: The donations to Fetterman came after a video recirculated showing Oz in a grocery store, complaining about the prices of ingredients needed to make "crudites."

TITLE: CDC Director Walensky to reorganize agency after admitting Covid pandemic response fell short
SUMMARY: The organizational changes are focused on sharing data more quickly and making public health guidance easier for people to understand.

TITLE: U.S. Navy is seeing more 'unsafe' aerial intercepts by China, says Seventh Fleet commander
SUMMARY: Karl Thomas said on Tuesday that he's seen a increase in "unsafe" aerial intercepts by Chinese military in the South China Sea region.

TITLE: Sarah Palin advances to November general election for Alaska House seat, NBC projects
SUMMARY: Like former President Donald Trump, Palin has worked as a political commentator and a reality-TV figure since she gave up the governorship.

TITLE: Murkowski and Trump-backed Tshibaka advance to Alaska general election, NBC projects
SUMMARY: Alaska Sen. Lisa Murkowski and a top Republican primary challenger endorsed by former President Donald Trump will advance to the general election, NBC projects.

TITLE: Rep. Liz Cheney loses GOP primary to Trump-backed challenger, NBC projects
SUMMARY: Cheney is Trump's highest-profile Republican critic in Congress and a leading figure in the House investigation of his role in the Jan. 6 Capitol riot.

TITLE: Biden signs Inflation Reduction Act into law, setting 15% minimum corporate tax rate
SUMMARY: After more than a year of debate, Biden's sweeping infrastructure bill is became law — albeit a significantly smaller version of his Build Back Better plan.

TITLE: Trump enemies Liz Cheney, Lisa Murkowski face GOP primary challengers as Sarah Palin stages comeback
SUMMARY: Rep. Liz Cheney, Trump's biggest GOP critic in the House and a leader on the Jan. 6 Capitol riot select committee, is expected to lose to Harriet Hageman.

TITLE: Biden's corporate tax hike in the Inflation Reduction Act won't hurt most U.S. companies, Wall Street analysts say
SUMMARY: Big U.S. companies fought the 15% corporate minimum tax in the Inflation Reduction Act, but tax experts say it won't hurt their bottom line all that much.

TITLE: DOJ urges judge to keep Trump search warrant affidavit sealed to protect national security investigation
SUMMARY: Federal prosecutors investigating former President Donald Trump asked a judge not to unseal an affidavit related to the FBI's search of Trump's Mar-a-Lago home.

TITLE: Rudy Giuliani named a target in Trump election probe in Georgia, lawyers say
SUMMARY: Giuliani was ex-President Donald Trump's personal attorney and a leading figure in various attempts to challenge his electoral loss to President Joe Biden.

TITLE: Judge denies Sen. Lindsey Graham's bid to quash subpoena in Trump election probe in Georgia
SUMMARY: Fulton County's DA wants to question Graham about phone calls he made to Georgia Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger after the Trump-Biden election.

TITLE: Trump search warrant cites statutes that carry possible multiyear prison sentences
SUMMARY: The FBI's search warrant served at Trump's Mar-a-Lago home highlights three statutes that hint at possible multiyear sentences.

TITLE: Read the FBI's search warrant for Trump's Mar-a-Lago home
SUMMARY: The FBI seized several sets of top-secret documents from former President Donald Trump's resort home when it was raided on Monday.

TITLE: FBI search warrant reveals agents seized top-secret documents in raid of Trump's home
SUMMARY: The FBI seized multiple sets of records marked top secret from former President Donald Trump's resort home Mar-a-Lago, a search warrant unsealed Friday shows.

TITLE: House passes massive climate, tax and health bill, sending Biden a core piece of his agenda to sign
SUMMARY: The bill's passage will mark a major win for Democrats and President Joe Biden less than three months before the pivotal midterm elections.

TITLE: DOJ plans to retry Philip Esformes despite Trump commuting sentence of Florida nursing home owner
SUMMARY: Florida nursing homes operator Philip Esformes was one of dozens of criminal defendants who received executive clemency from President Donald Trump.

TITLE: Salman Rushdie reportedly on a ventilator and unable to speak after he was stabbed
SUMMARY: Salman Rushdie was attacked at a Chautauqua Institution panel in western New York on Friday.

TITLE: Polio detected in New York City sewage suggesting local circulation of virus, health officials say
SUMMARY: Health officials are aggressively assessing how far polio has spread in the city and in New York state.

TITLE: U.S. is ‘not going anywhere,’ Middle East envoy says, as China’s Xi expected to visit Saudi Arabia
SUMMARY: The U.S. disputed claims that a forthcoming visit by Chinese President Xi Jinping to Saudi Arabia signals America's waning influence in the Middle East.

TITLE: Biden senior advisor Anita Dunn has to divest investment portfolio worth between $16.8 million and $48.2 million to avoid conflicts
SUMMARY: Dunn's financial disclosures show extensive stock, options, bond and private equity holdings — a fortune she and her husband have amassed over the years.

TITLE: Trump faces a slew of investigations and lawsuits —  and they're heating up as he weighs White House run
SUMMARY: The Republican Trump has called the investigations into his conduct politically motivated "witch hunts" by Democratic adversaries.

TITLE: Trump supports unsealing of search warrant for FBI raid on Mar-a-Lago after DOJ makes request
SUMMARY: The Justice Department had been under pressure to explain why the FBI raid the Florida home of former President Donald Trump.
